 theoretical foundations of the measure theory. It provides a complete set of classical and recent compactness results in measure and function spaces. The book is organized in three chapters: The first chapter covers background material on measure theory in abstract frame. In the second chapter the measure theory on topological spaces is presented. Compactness results from the first two chapters are used to study Young measures in the third chapter. All results are accompanied by full demonstrations and for many of these results different proofs are given. All statements are fully justified and proved.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMathematical optimization. 0aMeasure theory. 0aSpaces of measures. 4aBounded Measures. 4aMeasure Spaces. 4aTopological Spaces. 4aWeak Compactness. 4aYoung Measures. 7aMATHEMATICS / Functional Analysis.2bisacsh  aBounded Measure.  aFunctional Analysis.  aMeasure Space.  aTopological Space.  aWeak Compactness.  aYoung Measure.1 aGodet-Thobie, Christiane, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Mathematics 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023847108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Mathematics - 2000 - 2014z9783110637205oZDB-23-GMA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE MATHEMATICS, PHYSICS, ENGINEERING 2012z9783110293722oZDB-23-DMI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MATHEMATIK, PHYSIK, INGENIEURWISS. 2012z9783110288926oZDB-23-DMP0 cprintz978311027640440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/97